Nemesis Enforcer:



Slowly the blackness lifted as a hazy view of his surroundings were taken in 
by his optic sensors.  Nemesis Enforcer let out a groan, slowly getting to 
his feet.  He let out a yell as he noticed that one of the bat-like wings on 
his back had been severed in the crash.  Nemesis looked to his right hand and 
let out another yell as he saw that his middle finger was unnaturally bent 
back.

The Predacon gripped the finger with his good hand and with a short scream of 
pain bent it back into place.  Pain shot throughout his right hand as he 
closed it into a painful fist.  Nemesis Enforcer looked about the messy room 
he was in, not exactly sure where he was.  His thoughts were interrupted by 
Megatron's comm.  

"On my way." he responded into his comm. unit, leaving his room and going for 
the storage bay, but in fact he was unintentionally going the opposite 
direction the storage bay was in.
